<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36069a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36069a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36069a"> 69(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Old Bridge</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">According to tradition, Little John &hellip; shot an arrow from the <mark>old bridge</mark> (now Church Street Bridge) to the present site of St. Michan&apos;s Church, a distance of about eleven score and seven yards, but poor Little John&apos;s great practical skill in archery could not save him from an ignominious fate: as it appears from the records of the Southwell family, he was publicly executed for robbery on Arbour Hill. <small> James Collins, <a name="JCLO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCLO"><cite title="source">Life in Old Dublin</cite></a> (l913) 53</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
